body.name: Drip Pan Electric Stove Burner Covers for Whirlpool W10278125 W10196405 W10196406

features: 1. Compatibility: These replacement drip pans designed to fit most Whirlpool, Maytag, Kenmore, Sears, Amana, KitchenAid, Crosley plug-in electric ranges and cooktops. They are high-quality replacements for Whirlpool, Kenmore, and Sears oven range or stove.
2. Size: The package includes (2) 6" W10196406 and (2) 8" W10196405 stainless pans. The W10196406 6 inch pan measures 7.5 inches and the W10196405 8 inch pan measures 9.4 inches.

3. Compatibility: The pans are compatible with various part numbers including WPW10196406, WPW10196405, W10278125, and many more. They fit different models such as RC8920XAH0, RC8900XAB0, RC8900XAQ0, KECM860TBC0, RC8900XXW0, RS373PXWT2, RC8900XXB0, RS373PXWT1, RS373PXW3, RC8900XAH0, RC8900XAQ1, RC8900XXQ0, and RC8950XRH7.
4. Durable: These replacement drip pans are made of high-quality stainless steel materials, ensuring durability and long-lasting performance, no rust for a long time.
5.Easy to clean: The smooth surface of the stainless steel drip pans makes them easy to clean and maintain.
6.Protects the stove: The drip pans protect the electric stove burners from spills, drips, and stains, helping to keep the stove clean and in good condition.
7.Cost-effective: These replacement drip pans are an affordable alternative to purchasing a new stove or range, saving you money and extending the life of your appliance.
8.Simple installation: The drip pans are easy to install, simply remove the old pans and replace them with the new ones to improve the appearance and functionality of your stove.

Easy to clean Let the stovetop cool and remove the drip pans. Shake off any food debris and check for spills on the stovetop.Fill a sink or bucket with hot water and a few drops of dishwashing liquid. Soak the drip pans for 15 mins.Drain the soapy water and pour distilled white vinegar over the drip pans. Soak for 30 mins.Sprinkle baking soda over the solution and let it sit for at least 15 mins. Use a scrubber to remove tough stains.Rinse the drip pans with hot water and dry with a cloth.
Durable Material These replacement drip pans are made of high-quality stainless steel materials, ensuring durability and long-lasting performance, no rust for a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit nicely and good quality
reviews.reviewText: My stove is a Whirlpool so felt lucky to find drip pans that fit perfectly. They are nice quality and should last. My only complaint is that other drip pans I have purchased were shiny chrome, and these have more of a satin finish. The shiny ones always looked so new and clean. These look nice, but not the shiny new look I would like. I will keep them since they fit so nicely and are definitely a step up from my current drip pans.
